Leila wrote:

> Thanks,
>
> dumpKeys() helped.  But I do not know why the key
> looks like the following:
>
> quad_[Lcom.mydomain.Node;_int_int
>
> why it puts [L before com?

This is just how a class is identified internally in the JVM, and is 
used by methods like getName and forName in the class Class and other 
methods for reflection. For more information, see
http://java.sun.com/docs/books/vmspec/html/ClassFile.doc.html#13972
Actually I'm more surprised that int's are simply specified as int, 
after reading the link you'd expect it to be I. I guess they adapted it 
for readability.
